<br />
  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">ADVENTURE DECK STRATEGY<br />
<br />
You should bid to go first with this deck, I usually bid 2-3, depending on my opponent.  The Prancing Pony gives you Aragorn.  On your first turn, stop at Site 2, so you can bluff the opponent into double moving and play your Ford of Bruinen.  This will get out your Nazgul quick, doing damage early.  The Moria Stairway is in their to benefit both side, and most of the time you will have a weapon both in your Fellowship and for one of your minions. Sites 7-9 are Forests and Rivers, allowing you to play A Ranger&#39;s Versatility.  Site 7 also discards allies, so goodbye and good riddance to Mirror deck allies, Elrond, Hobbit Allies, and Elven Archers.  <br />
<br />
FELLOWSHIP STRATEGY<br />
<br />
Basically get out Aragorn and his bow as soon as possible.  The Tales will give him and Legolas an extra shot each turn.  Splendor and an Elven Bow are for Arwen, so she can add a few shots of her own.  A Ranger&#39;s Versatility will get exhaust minions, making them easy pickings for your Archery.  Defiance and Swordsman both can be played on Arwen, she is your go to girl for Skirmishes until Aragorn gets stacked with Ranger Sword and Last Alliance.  No Stranger to the Shadow can be played on Arwen and Aragorn, making it easier to double move on your opponent.  Sting and Power According to His Stature can keep Frodo alive, as long as you assign minions that survived the Archery Phase appropriately.<br />
<br />
SHADOW STRATEGY<br />
<br />
Use Nazgul to hold your opponent to one site at a time, allowing your Fellowship to race ahead.  Use the Blade Tip/Black Btreath combo to finish them off.  Wreathed in Shadow helps against Archery, but you can also use All Blades Perish.  <br />
Nazgul Swords are potentilly damage +1, so someone is going to die whenever you have these out.  Fear gets rid of annoying things like Galadriel, Bounder, Elrond, The Gaffer, and those Elf Archers.  Nobody has made it to Site 9 against this deck in tournament play.   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
